.START 

J. Patrick Kerich was named chairman and chief executive officer of this recreational vehicle company, effective Oct. 28.
He succeeds William L. Warrick, who announced his resignation in August.
Mr. Warrick, 48 years old, remains a director of the company.
Mr. Kerich, 51, most recently was sales vice president and a member of the executive committee of Skyline Corp., a rival maker of recreational vehicles. 

